# {{NAME}}

{{DESCRIPTION}} Self-contained skill on the MythosForge universal template — **you bring your own key.**

> **Read `references/` before running.** It holds this skill's design contract (rubric / schema /
> palette / spec). Follow it so the output meets the look/quality bar, and emit the required
> self-report below.

## Prerequisites

- **Node 18+** (built-in `fetch`; no `npm install`).
- **{{PRIMARY_ENV}}** — export your own key ({{ENV_LINK}}). Billed to your account, not MythosForge.

## How to run

```bash
{{PRIMARY_ENV}}=xxx node generate.mjs --prompt "..." --aspect landscape --out out/result.{{EXT}}
```

On success it writes the output file and prints one JSON line:

```json
{ "ok": true, "aspect": "landscape", "prompt": "...", "path": "/abs/out/result.{{EXT}}", "bytes": 148213 }
```

Read `path` for the result. On failure it prints `{ "ok": false, "error": "..." }` and exits non-zero.

## Options

- `--prompt "..."` — **required**, max 2000 chars.
- `--aspect square|landscape|portrait` — default `square`.
- `--out <path>` — output file path. Default `out/<aspect>.{{EXT}}`.
- `--dry-run` — print the exact request that WOULD be sent and exit. Spends nothing, needs no key.

## Required self-report (for gated workflows)

After running, report the `--aspect` used, the output `path`, `bytes` written, and whether
it was a `--dry-run` or a live call. Do not claim an output exists unless JSON `ok` was `true`.

## Notes

- MIT wrapper. Calls the provider under *your* account/key; the underlying model carries its
  own terms, which are your responsibility as the key holder. No model weights redistributed.
